header.gameNote: GREAT ALASKA SHOOTOUT AT ANCHORAGE AK

article.headline: Houston 73, Alaska-Anchorage 57
article.story: ANCHORAGE, Alaska -- Aubrey Coleman scored 25 points Saturday night as Houston beat Alaska Anchorage 73-57 for third place in the Great Alaska Shootout. Coleman was 11 of 16 shooting and made both of his 3-point attempts. Desmond Wade added 15 and Adam Brown finished with 14 for the Cougars (3-2), who led 37-25 at the break. Malcolm Campbell had a game-high 26 points, including 10 of 13 free throws, for the Seawolves (3-2). Brandon Walker chipped in 21 for Alaska Anchorage.
